01:31:46.000 --> 01:31:48.000
to electromagnetic radiation

01:31:48.000 --> 01:31:50.000
near the electrode.

01:31:50.000 --> 01:31:52.000
It means

01:31:52.000 --> 01:31:54.000
the battery

01:31:54.000 --> 01:31:56.000
lost a lot of energy.

01:31:56.000 --> 01:31:58.000
Second,

01:31:58.000 --> 01:32:00.000
its Q was too high.

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:02.000
I think it was

01:32:02.000 --> 01:32:04.000
between 100,000 and 1 million.

01:32:04.000 --> 01:32:06.000
It ran down very slowly.

01:32:06.000 --> 01:32:08.000
It seemed

01:32:08.000 --> 01:32:10.000
that such a system

01:32:10.000 --> 01:32:12.000
was not suitable

01:32:12.000 --> 01:32:14.000
for communication.

01:32:14.000 --> 01:32:16.000
It took a long time

01:32:16.000 --> 01:32:18.000
to go from 1 to 0.

01:32:18.000 --> 01:32:20.000
So they could only

01:32:20.000 --> 01:32:22.000
use frequency modulation.

01:32:22.000 --> 01:32:24.000
Frequency modulation

01:32:24.000 --> 01:32:26.000
may also be affected

01:32:26.000 --> 01:32:28.000
by its high Q.

01:32:28.000 --> 01:32:30.000
If you are interested,

01:32:30.000 --> 01:32:32.000
I think you can read

01:32:32.000 --> 01:32:34.000
their papers.

01:32:34.000 --> 01:32:36.000
We decided to use

01:32:36.000 --> 01:32:38.000
PZT later.

01:32:38.000 --> 01:32:40.000
We found a PZT manufacturer

01:32:40.000 --> 01:32:42.000
that could provide

01:32:42.000 --> 01:32:44.000
high-quality buck PZT.

01:32:44.000 --> 01:32:46.000
Its Q was over 1,000.

01:32:46.000 --> 01:32:48.000
It was very rare.

01:32:48.000 --> 01:32:50.000
We used PZT.

01:32:50.000 --> 01:32:52.000
But PZT had its own problem.

01:32:52.000 --> 01:32:54.000
Its dielectric constant was too high.

01:32:54.000 --> 01:32:56.000
So it

01:32:56.000 --> 01:32:58.000
had almost no so-called

01:32:58.000 --> 01:33:00.000
field-to-field effect.

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:02.000
It went from the moment

01:33:02.000 --> 01:33:04.000
it left Resonator

01:33:04.000 --> 01:33:06.000
to its original state.

01:33:06.000 --> 01:33:08.000
But I think

01:33:08.000 --> 01:33:10.000
PZT was not suitable

01:33:10.000 --> 01:33:12.000
for communication.

01:33:12.000 --> 01:33:14.000
Especially for measuring.

01:33:14.000 --> 01:33:16.000
We measured it for a month or two.

01:33:16.000 --> 01:33:18.000
But we found

01:33:18.000 --> 01:33:20.000
that it was wrong.

01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:22.000
Actually,

01:33:22.000 --> 01:33:24.000
I used

01:33:24.000 --> 01:33:26.000
